<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="77" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1611,2033]" pageId="5" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1683,1709]" pageId="5" pageNumber="77">Discussion:</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[393,491,1683,1709]" pageId="5" pageNumber="77">holotype</typeStatus>
is a brachypterous male with only the right foreleg intact. The left foreleg and right hindleg are complete only through the femur, the left middle leg is complete through the tibia, and the right middle leg and left hindleg are missing (
<figureCitation box="[521,630,1755,1781]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–8" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1330,1354]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,417,1307]" captionTargetId="figure-126@5.[151,1435,417,1307]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 7–8. Cryphocricos daguerrei holotype (7) dorsal and (8) ventral. Photos courtesy of H.D.D. Rodrigues." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4693084" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4693084/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="77">Figs. 7–8</figureCitation>
). The rivers in Concordia are wide, flat, and muddy, which are not suitable conditions for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Signoret" authorityYear="1850" box="[373,525,1791,1817]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Cryphocricos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[373,525,1791,1817]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="77">Cryphocricos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; thus, if indeed the type specimen was collected there, river dynamics probably have changed since its collection in 1931. 
<bibRefCitation author="De Carlo, J. A." box="[621,803,1827,1854]" pageId="5" pageNumber="77" pagination="99 - 104" refId="ref12526" refString="De Carlo, J. A. (1968) Descripcion de especies nuevas de los generos Ambrysus, Cryphocricos y Heleocoris. Allotypus de Cryphocricos daguerrei (Hemiptera - Naucoridae). Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina, 30, 99 - 104. [1967]" type="journal article" year="1968">De Carlo (1968)</bibRefCitation>
proposed an 
<typeStatus box="[951,1041,1827,1853]" pageId="5" pageNumber="77">allotype</typeStatus>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1108,1210,1827,1853]" name="Uruguay" pageId="5" pageNumber="77">Uruguay</collectingCountry>
; however, this is not permissible under the rules of the ICZN, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Lopez Ruf, M. L." box="[660,860,1863,1889]" pageId="5" pageNumber="77" pagination="103 - 120" refId="ref13109" refString="Lopez Ruf, M. L. (1991) El genero Cryphocricos en la Argentina (Hemiptera-Limnocoridae). Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina, 49 (1 - 4), 103 - 120." type="journal article" year="1991">Lopez Ruf (1991)</bibRefCitation>
challenged the accuracy of the identification based on differences in color, pronotum, and head shape with those of the 
<typeStatus box="[912,1014,1899,1925]" pageId="5" pageNumber="77">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="78" pageId="5" pageNumber="77" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1611,2033]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,151,322]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="78" pageId="5" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,324,1935,1961]" pageId="5" pageNumber="77">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="De Carlo, J. A." box="[333,521,1935,1961]" pageId="5" pageNumber="77" pagination="37 - 41" refId="ref12325" refString="De Carlo, J. A. (1941) I) Descripcion de dos especies nuevas del genero Limnocoris Stal. II) nuevas consideraciones sobre Cryphocricus daguerrei y Cryphocricus rufus De Carlo (Hemiptera-Naucoridae). Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina, 11, 37 - 41." type="journal article" year="1941">De Carlo (1941)</bibRefCitation>
offered the diagnostic character of abdominal segments II and III (he probably meant III and IV) lateral margins individually slightly curved; thus, creating a non-uniform curvature of the entire abdominal lateral margin. This species differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="De Carlo, 1940" authorityName="De Carlo" authorityYear="1940" box="[745,1022,2007,2033]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Cryphocricos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rufus">
<emphasis box="[745,837,2007,2033]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="77">C. rufus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="De Carlo, J. A." box="[846,1022,2007,2033]" pageId="5" pageNumber="77" pagination="426 - 433" refId="ref12276" refString="De Carlo, J. A. (1940) I) Descripcion de tres especies nuevas del genero Cryphocricus Signoret. II). Una nueva especie del genero Heleocoris Stal (Hemiptera-Naucoridae). Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina, 10, 426 - 433." type="journal article" year="1940">De Carlo, 1940</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by its smaller size, the shape of the hemelytra, the concavity in the prothoracic anterior margin, the shape of the head, and fewer granulations (=tubercles) (
<bibRefCitation author="De Carlo, J. A." box="[255,425,187,213]" pageId="6" pageNumber="78" pagination="426 - 433" refId="ref12276" refString="De Carlo, J. A. (1940) I) Descripcion de tres especies nuevas del genero Cryphocricus Signoret. II). Una nueva especie del genero Heleocoris Stal (Hemiptera-Naucoridae). Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina, 10, 426 - 433." type="journal article" year="1940">De Carlo 1940</bibRefCitation>
). This species differs from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="De Carlo" baseAuthorityYear="1968" box="[730,842,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Cryphocricos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fittkaui">
<emphasis box="[730,842,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="78">C. fittkaui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its darker color and the female subgenital plate is very similar, although it has its differences (
<bibRefCitation author="De Carlo, J. A." box="[654,827,223,250]" pageId="6" pageNumber="78" pagination="189 - 200" refId="ref12493" refString="De Carlo, J. A. (1967) Una nueva especie del genero Ranatra y nuevas especies de Naucoridae. Amazoniana, 1 (2), 189 - 200." type="journal article" year="1967">De Carlo 1967</bibRefCitation>
). The female subgenital plate was illustrated with the lateral margins sinuate and the posterior margin to have three distinct lobes, with the middle lobe half the length of the lateral lobes, and is comparable to that of 
<taxonomicName authority="(De Carlo 1968)" baseAuthorityName="De Carlo" baseAuthorityYear="1968" box="[661,967,295,322]" class="Insecta" family="Naucoridae" genus="Cryphocricos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fittkaui">
<emphasis box="[661,773,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="78">C. fittkaui</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="De Carlo, J. A." box="[788,958,295,322]" pageId="6" pageNumber="78" pagination="99 - 104" refId="ref12526" refString="De Carlo, J. A. (1968) Descripcion de especies nuevas de los generos Ambrysus, Cryphocricos y Heleocoris. Allotypus de Cryphocricos daguerrei (Hemiptera - Naucoridae). Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina, 30, 99 - 104. [1967]" type="journal article" year="1968">De Carlo 1968</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
